Add half the cheese and all the buttered spinach. Put your 16–20cm base omelette pan on to high heat. Add the oil. Once it’s hot, add the egg/ spinach mix. Reduce the heat to low after 20 seconds. Leave to cook on low for 1–2 minutes or until the base is just set and the top still runny. Sprinkle with the rest of the parmesan and dot with butter. Finish under the grill for 1–2 minutes until browned at the edges with the top glazed, golden and puffy.
